revisions.description: 02a85 Added the objects wsCcRfRadioState, wsCcRfSmartRadioCurrChannel, and wsCcRfSmartRadioCurrPower.
02a84 Added the object wsCcRfSmartCalibrationStatusMessage to provide current status of calibration on the member switch.
02a83 Added the object wsCcRfSmartRadioSwichIpAddr in wsCcRfSmartRadioTable.
02a79 Added wsCcRfSensorRevertVlan to configure vlans where sensors are to be discovered.
02a78 Removed the unused object wsCcRfRadioDefaultCovRate. Added the object wsCcRfRadioLedMode to help locate an AP.
02a76 Added objects for Adaptive APN (AP7131 and AP7181). Updated description of wsCcRfApVoiceDelay. Added the object wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusDynamicAuthEnable.
02a75 Added three more smart-rf related objects.
02a73 Added an entry MaxRetries(6) in the WlanWmmConfig
02a72 Added an entry sensor(5) in the list of wsCcRfRadioStatusState
02a71 Modified the range of wsCcRfMuRateLimitingUp and wsCcRfMuRateLimitingDown from (0..100000) to (0 | 100..100000).
02a70 Changed the max-access for wsCcRfSmartIsClusterMaster and wsCcRfSmartMasterSwitchAddr to read-only, since they are not configurable under wireless config. Added wsCcRfSmartRadioNeighborMac.

02a69 Renamed wsCcRfSensorRevert to wsCcRfSensor. Created wsCcRfSensorRevert under wsCcRfSensor. Moved all existing OIDs under wsCcRfSensorRevert to under the new OID for wsCcRfSensorRevert. Added new node wsCcRfSensorCfg under wsCcRfSensor. Under wsCcRfSensorCfg added wsCcRfSensorCfgWipsServerPrimaryIp and wsCcRfSensorCfgWipsServerSecondaryIp.
02a68 Replaced wsCcRfSmartPowerRange with wsCcRfSmartPowerRangeLowerBound and wsCcRfSmartPowerRangeHigherBound Added two tables for user-selectable channel feature.
02a67 Added the OID wsCcRfRadioWipsTable for AAP WIPS sensor support in wsCcRfRadio
02a66 Added an OID for max roamed devices in wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlTable and wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlTable.
02a65 Added some for smart RF scalars, one global ccRf scalar and the smart RF neighbor table.
02a64 Added new table for Admission Control statistics.
02a63 Added three new scalars for wsCcRfSmart
02a61 Modified the description of wsCcRfApAapImgEnableAutoUpd to explain allowed behaviour.
02a60 Re-organized OIDs for TSPEC Admission Control.
02a58 Added OIDs for TSPEC Admission Control.
02a57 Corrected the MAX-ACCESS of wsCcRfMuLocationingPreferredIndex to read-only.

02a55 Corrected the name of wsCcRfWlanAuthNACServerPort1 to wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort1. Changed the type and range of each of wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort1 and wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort2 to INTEGER and 1024-65535, respectively
02a54 Deprecate the value switchToWired(3) of wsCcRfWlanMuToMu. Using switchToWired(3) is identical in behavior to the value allow(2).
02a53 Added three new enums to IdsViolationType
02a52 Added Simultaneous Users support in Hotspot table
02a51 Added wsCcRfHotspotRedirectToHostName to enable or disable the use of hostname/System-Name in the redirection URL instead of the IP address of the switch.
02a50 Added the following MIB objects for AP-5131 firmware update: - wsCcRfApImgUploadTable - wsCcRfApImgUploadLastFailedReason - wsCcRfApAapImg and sub-objects
02a49 Added MIB Items wsCcRfHotspotLogoutOnClose and wsCcRfHotspotMaxLoginAttempts to the wsCcRfHotspotTable.
02a48 Redefined wsCcRfApExtTable by indexing it with new column wsCcRfApExtApMac.
02a47 In wsCcRfMuLoadBalancingMethod, changed the enumerated name byThreshold to byThroughput.
02a46 Bumped up max link timeout for client bridge to 200 seconds.
02a45 Modified the value range of wsCcRfRadioGroupId.
02a44 Removed wsCcRfRadioMeshWlan as it is no longer needed for AAP config.
02a42 Corrected the type for rate-limiting objects.
02a39 Fixed the indexing of wsCcRfRadioGroupTable so that it can show multiple radios per group.
02a38 Added objects for rate-limiting,load balancing and hotspot external login page tag.
02a37 Removed violFilterAvgNoiseLevel from IdsViolationType enum. Deleted wsCcRfRadioMaxSipSessions and wsCcRfRadioStatusActiveSipSessions as they are not reqd.
02a34 Defined the range for wsCcRfWlanVlanUserLimit and updated its description to explain the different limits for different wireless switch platforms.
02a30 Deprecated wsCcRfWlanGRETunnelIdx, wsCcRfWlanGRETunnelGatewayIp and wsCcRfWlanGRETunnelGatewayMask since WLAN over GRE feature is no longer supported.
added Multiple VLANs per WLAN feature MIB objects

RadioWmmConfig.name: RadioWmmConfig
RadioWmmConfig.description: Configuration parameter specification for 802.11e / Wireless MultiMedia, which control the Quality of Service between the wireless devices on the network. field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1 Aifsn 1..15 2 2 CwMax 0..15 3 3 CwMin 0..15 4 4-5 TxOp 0..65535 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | Aifsn (1 octet) | CwMax (1 octet) | CwMin (1 octet) | TxOp (2 octets) | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- All octets are in network byte order. Definition of contents: Aifsn: The Arbitration Inter-Frame Spacing is the wait time in milliSeconds between data frames. A smaller number leads to greater priority for medium access. CwMax: On each collision the AP or MU doubles its initial contention window wait time, until that number is as large as this maximum contention window size. For ease of use this value is configured as a number between 0 and 10; the actual window is calculated using 2**x -1 where x is the value configured. CwMin: If the medium is busy, or a transmitted frame collides, the AP or MU choose a random number between 0 and this minimum contention window size, to decide how long to wait before attempting (re)-transmission. For ease of use this value is configured as a number between 0 and 10; the actual window is calculated using 2**x -1 where x is the value configured. TxOp: An interval of time where an 802.11e station (MU/AP) has the right to initiate transmissions on the wireless medium.

Definition of contents: Aifsn: The Arbitration Inter-Frame Spacing is the wait time in milliSeconds between data frames. A smaller number leads to greater priority for medium access. CwMax: On each collision the AP or MU doubles its initial contention window wait time, until that number is as large as this maximum contention window size. For ease of use this value is configured as a number between 0 and 10; the actual window is calculated using 2**x -1 where x is the value configured. CwMin: If the medium is busy, or a transmitted frame collides, the AP or MU choose a random number between 0 and this minimum contention window size, to decide how long to wait before attempting (re)-transmission. For ease of use this value is configured as a number between 0 and 10; the actual window is calculated using 2**x -1 where x is the value configured. TxOp: An interval of time where an 802.11e station (MU/AP) has the right to initiate transmissions on the wireless medium. MaxRetries: Set the Maximum number of retries for a particular wlan per access category.

wsCcRfApImgUploadFile.name: wsCcRfApImgUploadFile
wsCcRfApImgUploadFile.description: Image file path. It can be specified as one of the following: flash:/path/file cf:/path/file usb1:/path/file usb2:/path/file

wsCcRfApImgUploadRowStatus.name: wsCcRfApImgUploadRowStatus
wsCcRfApImgUploadRowStatus.description: The Row status. All columns must be supplied to create a row. Row creation uploads the file to the Switch. If upload fails, row creation will fail and wsCcRfApImgUploadLastFailedReason will have the reason. Row deletion restores the original AP Image. In case AAP, the image is not uploaded to the switch. AAP image update will fetch the image from the specified location.

wsCcRfApAapImgEnableAutoUpd.name: wsCcRfApAapImgEnableAutoUpd
wsCcRfApAapImgEnableAutoUpd.description: Enable or disable automatic image update of AAP. The value of this object can be set to 'true' even if no images have previously been configured in wsCcRfApImgUploadTable.

wsCcRfApAapImgUpdStart.name: wsCcRfApAapImgUpdStart
wsCcRfApAapImgUpdStart.description: Image update start. Setting this value to 2 means starting image update. The following must be configured before setting this value to 2: - wsCcRfApAapImgUpdMac contains the MAC address of the AAP and the AAP must be adopted. - wsCcRfApImgUploadTable contains the AAP image name. If image update fails, wsCcRfApAapImgUpdLastFailedReason will have the reason. If there is no image update, its value will be set to 1.

wsCcRfRadioAutoAdopt.name: wsCcRfRadioAutoAdopt
wsCcRfRadioAutoAdopt.description: Enable or disable the switch to auto-adopt radios.

wsCcRfRadioCnt.name: wsCcRfRadioCnt
wsCcRfRadioCnt.description: Number of radios adopted by the switch. This is a count of the number of rows in wsCcRfRadioStatusTable

wsCcRfRadioLastMac.name: wsCcRfRadioLastMac
wsCcRfRadioLastMac.description: This scalar records the MAC address of the most recent radio to be Adopted, UnAdopted, or Denied.

wsCcRfRadioLastReason.name: wsCcRfRadioLastReason
wsCcRfRadioLastReason.description: This value notes the reason for the most-recent radio UnAdoption or Denial.

wsCcRfRadioTable.name: wsCcRfRadioTable
wsCcRfRadioTable.description: This table lists all radios adopted by this wireless switch.

wsCcRfRadioApMac.name: wsCcRfRadioApMac
wsCcRfRadioApMac.description: MAC address of the Access Port that this radio resides within.

wsCcRfRadioType.name: wsCcRfRadioType
wsCcRfRadioType.description: Radio model. Changing this value will result in all parameters getting defaulted for this radio.

wsCcRfRadioApType.name: wsCcRfRadioApType
wsCcRfRadioApType.description: Model of the Access Port this radio resides in.

wsCcRfRadioBssWlanMap.name: wsCcRfRadioBssWlanMap
wsCcRfRadioBssWlanMap.description: The mapping of WLANs to BSSIDs. Each radio supports 4 BSSIDs and 16 WLANs. The user can map any number of WLANs to each of the BSSIDs. Each BSSID forms a virtual ap.

wsCcRfRadioAntDiversity.name: wsCcRfRadioAntDiversity
wsCcRfRadioAntDiversity.description: The antenna diversity setting for the Access Port. Options for 11n radio: - Valid options are primaryOnly and mimo - Default option is mimo - For single antenna operation set mode to primaryOnly

wsCcRfRadioShortPreamble.name: wsCcRfRadioShortPreamble
wsCcRfRadioShortPreamble.description: Enable support for Short Preamble when MUs associate with the Access Port. Enabling Short Preamble may cause incompatibility with some older clients. Applies only to b/g radios.

wsCcRfRadioRtsThresh.name: wsCcRfRadioRtsThresh
wsCcRfRadioRtsThresh.description: The Request To Send(RTS) threshold(in bytes) for use by this radio.

wsCcRfRadioBeaconInt.name: wsCcRfRadioBeaconInt
wsCcRfRadioBeaconInt.description: Specify a beacon interval in units of 1,000 microseconds (K-us). This is a multiple of the DTIM (wsCcRfRadioDtimPrd) value, for example, 100 : 10.

wsCcRfRadioDtimPrd.name: wsCcRfRadioDtimPrd
wsCcRfRadioDtimPrd.description: Specify a period for the Delivery Traffic Indication Message (DTIM). This is a divisor of the beacon interval (in milliseconds), for example, 10 : 100.

wsCcRfRadioBasicRates.name: wsCcRfRadioBasicRates
wsCcRfRadioBasicRates.description: List of basic rates for the radio.

wsCcRfRadioSupportedRates.name: wsCcRfRadioSupportedRates
wsCcRfRadioSupportedRates.description: List of supported rates for the radio.

wsCcRfRadioRapDetector.name: wsCcRfRadioRapDetector
wsCcRfRadioRapDetector.description: If this radio is a Rogue AP detector.

wsCcRfRadioMaxMu.name: wsCcRfRadioMaxMu
wsCcRfRadioMaxMu.description: Max number of Mu a radio can associate.

wsCcRfRadioSelfHealingAction.name: wsCcRfRadioSelfHealingAction
wsCcRfRadioSelfHealingAction.description: Action taken by this radio when neighbor radios go down

wsCcRfRadioSelfHealingPwrOffset.name: wsCcRfRadioSelfHealingPwrOffset
wsCcRfRadioSelfHealingPwrOffset.description: Self-healing power offset for this radio

wsCcRfRadioRunAcsNow.name: wsCcRfRadioRunAcsNow
wsCcRfRadioRunAcsNow.description: Set wsCcRfRadioRunAcsNow to 1 to run Acs.

wsCcRfRadioResetParentAp.name: wsCcRfRadioResetParentAp
wsCcRfRadioResetParentAp.description: Set wsCcRfRadioResetParentAp to 1 to reset the parent Access Port of this radio.

wsCcRfRadioReset.name: wsCcRfRadioReset
wsCcRfRadioReset.description: Set wsCcRfRadioReset to 1 to reset the Radio.

wsCcRfRadioRapSingleChannelScan.name: wsCcRfRadioRapSingleChannelScan
wsCcRfRadioRapSingleChannelScan.description: Enable or disable single-channel scan for Rogue AP.

wsCcRfRadioBssDtim.name: wsCcRfRadioBssDtim
wsCcRfRadioBssDtim.description: Set DTIM per BSS. DTIM period is not configurable on a per BSS basis for AP71X1 11n radios. These radios use a single DTIM period across all BSS in a radio which can be configured in wsCcRfRadioDtimPrd.

wsCcRfRadioCfgMethod.name: wsCcRfRadioCfgMethod
wsCcRfRadioCfgMethod.description: The radio can be configured by user before being adopted or by the switch while adoption

wsCcRfRadioMuLocationingEnable.name: wsCcRfRadioMuLocationingEnable
wsCcRfRadioMuLocationingEnable.description: Enable/Disable MU locationing on this radio

wsCcRfRadioRogueApLocationingEnable.name: wsCcRfRadioRogueApLocationingEnable
wsCcRfRadioRogueApLocationingEnable.description: Enable/Disable rogue AP locationing on this radio

wsCcRfRadioRssEnable.name: wsCcRfRadioRssEnable
wsCcRfRadioRssEnable.description: Setting this object to True enables (False for disable) RSS (Remote Site Survivability) for this radio.

wsCcRfRadioGroupId.name: wsCcRfRadioGroupId
wsCcRfRadioGroupId.description: The group id that this radio belongs to. This field is used for the load-balancing feature wherein radios are combined in groups and MUs are discouraged from association if it not coming from the least loaded radio in the group. Group id 0 is used to indicate that this radio does not belong to any group.

wsCcRfRadioLedMode.name: wsCcRfRadioLedMode
wsCcRfRadioLedMode.description: The mode of operation of the LEDs on the AP. The meanings of the values are: startFlashing - When the value startFlashing is written to this object, the parent AP of the radio begins flashing its LEDs to help locate it. stopFlashing- When the value stopFlashing is written to this object, the parent AP of the radio reverts its LEDs to normal mode of operation. idleState - When the value idleState is written to this object, no action is taken. When read, this object always returns the value idleState.

wsCcRfRadioState.name: wsCcRfRadioState
wsCcRfRadioState.description: The state of the radio. unseen : Configured, but not connected unadopted : Connected, but not adopted normal : Adopted and working normal detector : Adopted and is working as a detector selfHealing : Legacy self-healing rescuing : Adopted and is rescuing to recover for neighbor filling : Adopted and is filling in to recover coverage hole sensor : Sensor

wsCcRfRadioChannelPowerTable.name: wsCcRfRadioChannelPowerTable
wsCcRfRadioChannelPowerTable.description: Use wsCcRfRadioChannelPower table to view and set the channel/power/placement properties of the radios. The process can be broken down into the following steps: 1. Set wsCcRfRadioCpReset to TRUE. 2. Set wsCcRfRadioCpPlacement 3. Get wsCcRfRadioCpPosChannel 4. Set wsCcRfRadioCpDesChannel 5. Get wsCcRfRadioCpPosPowerLevel 6. Set wsCcRfRadioCpDesPowerLevel 7. Get wsCcRfRadioCpPowerInMW 8. Set wsCcRfRadioCp11nChannelWidth 9. Set wsCcRfRadioCp11nSecondaryChannel 10. Set wsCcRfRadioCpSet

wsCcRfRadioCpChannelMode.name: wsCcRfRadioCpChannelMode
wsCcRfRadioCpChannelMode.description: fixed mode: apply user selected channel random mode: random channel selection acs mode: auto channel selection (radio will scan for the least congested channel at startup or reconfiguration)

wsCcRfRadioCpPosChannel.name: wsCcRfRadioCpPosChannel
wsCcRfRadioCpPosChannel.description: The possible channels that can be set when placement = wsCcRfRadioCpPlacement.

wsCcRfRadioCpPosPowerDb.name: wsCcRfRadioCpPosPowerDb
wsCcRfRadioCpPosPowerDb.description: The max possible power level (dBm) that can be set when channel= wsCcRfRadioCpDesChannel.

wsCcRfRadioCpDesPowerDb.name: wsCcRfRadioCpDesPowerDb
wsCcRfRadioCpDesPowerDb.description: The desired power level (dBm) for radio.

wsCcRfRadioCpSet.name: wsCcRfRadioCpSet
wsCcRfRadioCpSet.description: Validate values in wsCcRfRadioCpDes fields. If it is a valid combination, configure the switch with this combination and set wsCcRfRadioCp_ to these values.

wsCcRfRadioCpReset.name: wsCcRfRadioCpReset
wsCcRfRadioCpReset.description: Reset the following OIDs. wsCcRfRadioCpDesPlacement wsCcRfRadioCpDesChannel wsCcRfRadioCpDesPowerLevel wsCcRfRadioCpPosChannel wsCcRfRadioCpPosPowerLevel wsCcRfRadioCpPowerInMW wsCcRfRadioCp11nChannelWidth wsCcRfRadioCp11nSecondaryChannel

wsCcRfRadioWmmTable.name: wsCcRfRadioWmmTable
wsCcRfRadioWmmTable.description: Configuration parameters for 802.11e / Wireless MultiMedia, which control the Quality of Service between the wireless devices on the network

wsCcRfRadioWmmBeParm.description: Parameters for the Best Effort QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. Prior to setting this field, please be sure to get the current value.

wsCcRfRadioWmmBkParm.name: wsCcRfRadioWmmBkParm
wsCcRfRadioWmmBkParm.description: Parameters for the Background QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. Prior to setting this field, please be sure to get the current value.

wsCcRfRadioWmmViParm.name: wsCcRfRadioWmmViParm
wsCcRfRadioWmmViParm.description: Parameters for the Video QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. Prior to setting this field, please be sure to get the current value.

wsCcRfRadioWmmVoParm.name: wsCcRfRadioWmmVoParm
wsCcRfRadioWmmVoParm.description: Parameters for the Voice QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. Prior to setting this field, please be sure to get the current value.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultTable.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultTable
wsCcRfRadioDefaultTable.description: This table lists the default setting for all supported radio for this switch. Please refer to wsCcRfRadioTable for column descriptions.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultRapSingleChannelScan.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultRapSingleChannelScan
wsCcRfRadioDefaultRapSingleChannelScan.description: Enable or disable single-channel scan for Rogue AP.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultBssDtim.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultBssDtim
wsCcRfRadioDefaultBssDtim.description: Set DTIM per BSS. DTIM period is not configurable on a per BSS basis for AP71X1 11n radios. These radios use a single DTIM period across all BSS in a radio which can be configured in wsCcRfRadioDefaultDtimPrd.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultMuLocationingEnable.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultMuLocationingEnable
wsCcRfRadioDefaultMuLocationingEnable.description: Enable/Disable MU locationing on this radio

wsCcRfRadioDefaultRogueApLocationingEnab.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultRogueApLocationingEnable
wsCcRfRadioDefaultRogueApLocationingEnab.description: Enable/Disable Rogue AP locationing on this radio

wsCcRfRadioDefaultAntGain.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultAntGain
wsCcRfRadioDefaultAntGain.description: Antenna gain. Please see the definition of RadioAntennaGain for additional information.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultChannelPowerTable.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultChannelPowerTable
wsCcRfRadioDefaultChannelPowerTable.description: Use wsCcRfRadioDefaultChannelPower table to view and set the channel/power/placement properties of the default radio configurations. Please refer to the descriptions in wsCcRfRadioChannelPowerTable

wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmTable.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmTable
wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmTable.description: Configuration parameters for 802.11e / Wireless MultiMedia, which control the Quality of Service between the wireless devices on the network

wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmAccessCategory.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmAccessCategory
wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmAccessCategory.description: A label for a particular QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. WMM defines 4 Access Categories (Voice, Video, Best Effort, Background).

wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmAifsn.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmAifsn
wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmAifsn.description: The Arbitration Inter-Frame Spacing is the wait time in milliSeconds between data frames. A smaller number leads to greater priority for medium access.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmTxOp.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmTxOp
wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmTxOp.description: An interval of time where an 802.11e station (MU/AP) has the right to initiate transmissions on the wireless medium.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmCwMin.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmCwMin
wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmCwMin.description: If the medium is busy, or a transmitted frame collides, the AP or MU choose a random number between 0 and this minimum contention window size, to decide how long to wait before attempting (re)-transmission. For ease of use this value is configured as a number between 0 and 10; the actual window is calculated using 2**x -1 where x is the value configured.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmCwMax.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmCwMax
wsCcRfRadioDefaultWmmCwMax.description: On each collision the AP or MU doubles its initial contention window wait time, until that number is as large as this maximum contention window size. For ease of use this value is configured as a number between 0 and 10; the actual window is calculated using 2**x -1 where x is the value configured.

wsCcRfRadioStatusState.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusState
wsCcRfRadioStatusState.description: This value describes the state of the radio. A healthy radio would power-on, and quickly advance from radioUpAndWaitingForConfig and then on to radioReceivingConfig and then on to radioUpAndAdopted. A radio that is denied adoption due to ACLs would show: radioDeniedAdoptionDueToAcl. A radio that does not 'handshake' with the switch properly would be found in state: radioBroken.

wsCcRfRadioStatusPtrToAp.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusPtrToAp
wsCcRfRadioStatusPtrToAp.description: This value is the index in the ApTable for the entry representing the Access Port that contains this radio. Since each radio has one and only one Access Port as 'parent', this value is a simple integer, not a bit-mask.

wsCcRfRadioStatusMaxWlans.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusMaxWlans
wsCcRfRadioStatusMaxWlans.description: the maximum number of 802.11 ESSIDs (wireless lans) supported by this radio

wsCcRfRadioStatusMaxBss.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusMaxBss
wsCcRfRadioStatusMaxBss.description: The maximum number of 802.11 BSSIDs supported by this radio

wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrChannel.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrChannel
wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrChannel.description: current channel (may be different from configured channel due to DFS etc).

wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrPowerDb.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrPowerDb
wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrPowerDb.description: Output power level for the radio in Db.

wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrPowerMw.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrPowerMw
wsCcRfRadioStatusCurrPowerMw.description: Output power level for the radio in Mw.

wsCcRfRadioStatusShortSlotTime.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusShortSlotTime
wsCcRfRadioStatusShortSlotTime.description: Indicates the 802.11g short-slot time on the radio

wsCcRfRadioStatusVlanTag.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusVlanTag
wsCcRfRadioStatusVlanTag.description: The VLAN tag using which the switch is communicating with the radio

wsCcRfRadioStatusCfgMethod.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusCfgMethod
wsCcRfRadioStatusCfgMethod.description: The radio can be configured by user before being adopted or by the switch while adoption.

wsCcRfRadioStatusAssociatedVoiceMus.name: wsCcRfRadioStatusAssociatedVoiceMus
wsCcRfRadioStatusAssociatedVoiceMus.description: Number of MUs identified as voice associated.

wsCcRf802dt1xRadioAuthSetRadio.name: wsCcRf802dt1xRadioAuthSetRadio
wsCcRf802dt1xRadioAuthSetRadio.description: Set the username and password stored in wsCcRf802dt1xRadioAuthLogin and wsCcRf802dt1xRadioAuthPass on all radios adopted by the switch.

wsCcRfRadioConfiguredCnt.name: wsCcRfRadioConfiguredCnt
wsCcRfRadioConfiguredCnt.description: Number of configured radios. This is a count of the number of rows in wsCcRfRadioTable.

wsCcRfRadioBridgeTable.name: wsCcRfRadioBridgeTable
wsCcRfRadioBridgeTable.description: This table gives information related to the bridging capabilities of the radios adopted by the wireless switch.

wsCcRfRadioBridgeClientBridgeEnable.name: wsCcRfRadioBridgeClientBridgeEnable
wsCcRfRadioBridgeClientBridgeEnable.description: Enables or disables client-bridge functionality on the radio.

wsCcRfRadioBridgeBaseBridgeEnable.name: wsCcRfRadioBridgeBaseBridgeEnable
wsCcRfRadioBridgeBaseBridgeEnable.description: Allows the given radio to act as a base bridge and accept connections from client bridges.

wsCcRfRadioBridgeSsid.name: wsCcRfRadioBridgeSsid
wsCcRfRadioBridgeSsid.description: Set the bridge SSID (max length 32 characters).

wsCcRfRadioBridgeLinkTimeout.name: wsCcRfRadioBridgeLinkTimeout
wsCcRfRadioBridgeLinkTimeout.description: Set the bridge link timeout in seconds.

wsCcRfRadioBridgeMaxClientBridges.name: wsCcRfRadioBridgeMaxClientBridges
wsCcRfRadioBridgeMaxClientBridges.description: Set the maximum client-bridge connections permissible.

wsCcRfRadioGroupTable.name: wsCcRfRadioGroupTable
wsCcRfRadioGroupTable.description: A read only table showing radios to their group id mapping.

wsCcRfRadioGroupTableGrpId.name: wsCcRfRadioGroupTableGrpId
wsCcRfRadioGroupTableGrpId.description: The group id to which this radio belongs.

wsCcRfRadioGroupRadioId.name: wsCcRfRadioGroupRadioId
wsCcRfRadioGroupRadioId.description: The radio id (value same as wsCcRfRadioIndex) which belongs to this group.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlTable.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlTable
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlTable.description: Configure admission control parameters for devices sending voice traffic.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlAccessCategor.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlAccessCategory
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlAccessCategor.description: A label for a particular QoS category of traffic. WMM standard suggests to perform admission control for maintaining QoS of traffic sent using Video and Voice access category.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxAirTime.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxAirTime
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxAirTime.description: Maximum percentage of air time that can be distributed among devices sending traffic using a particular access category. For example, configuring a value of 70% for voice, means that a total 700 ms out of 1000 ms will be distributed among devices which setup voice calls. This helps in maintaining the QoS of existing calls on a particular radio.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlReservedRoamT.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlReservedRoamTime
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlReservedRoamT.description: Maxmimum percentage of air time reserved for devices which have roamed. This value should be less than the value specified for wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxAirTime.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxAdmittedDe.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxAdmittedDevices
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxAdmittedDe.description: Max devices that the radio will admit for sending voice traffic without leading to oversubscription. A value of 0 would disable admission control for the access category.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxRoamedDevi.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxRoamedDevices
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxRoamedDevi.description: Maximum roamed devices that the radio will admit for sending voice traffic after the count of admitted devices has reached wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlMaxAdmittedDevices.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlTable.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlTable
wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlTable.description: Configure default admission control parameters for different radios.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlAccess.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlAccessCategory
wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlAccess.description: A label for a particular QoS category of traffic. WMM standard suggests to perform admission control for maintaining QoS of traffic sent using Video and Voice access category.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxAir.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxAirTime
wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxAir.description: The default maximum percentage of air time for a particular access category.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlReserv.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlReservedRoamTime
wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlReserv.description: The default percentage of air time reserved for roaming for a particular access category.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxAdm.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxAdmittedDevices
wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxAdm.description: The default maximum number of devices that can be admitted to send traffic using a particular access category.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxRoa.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxRoamedDevices
wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxRoa.description: The default maximum roamed devices that a radio will admit for sending voice traffic after the count of admitted devices has reached wsCcRfRadioDefaultAdmissionControlMaxAdmittedDevices.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusAccessC.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusAccessCategory
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusAccessC.description: Admission control statistics for WMM voice access category.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusAirTime.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusAirTimeUsage
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusAirTime.description: The total percentage of air time used on the radio by devices which have been admitted.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusRoamedD.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusRoamedDevices
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusRoamedD.description: Total count of roamed devices which have been admitted.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusRequest.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusRequestDenied
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlStatusRequest.description: Total count of requests which have been denied either due to insufficient air time or maximum device capacity.

wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlEnable.name: wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlEnable
wsCcRfRadioAdmissionControlEnable.description: Enable admission control for voice traffic. This also enables WMM admission control for Voice access category. A value of 0 disables admission control across all radios.

wsCcRfRadioWipsTable.name: wsCcRfRadioWipsTable
wsCcRfRadioWipsTable.description: This table gives information related to the WIPS mode of the radios adopted by the wireless switch.

wsCcRfRadioRfFunctionWipsEnable.name: wsCcRfRadioRfFunctionWipsEnable
wsCcRfRadioRfFunctionWipsEnable.description: Converts the given radio from the WLAN mode to the WIPS mode.

wsCcRfRadio11nTable.name: wsCcRfRadio11nTable
wsCcRfRadio11nTable.description: This table lists all 11n radios adopted by this wireless switch. A row in this table is an extension of a row in wsCcRfRadioTable with the relationship being sparse.

wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduMinSpacing.name: wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduMinSpacing
wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduMinSpacing.description: The minimum spacing between the start of adjacent MPDUs within an A-MPDU.

wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduRxLimit.name: wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduRxLimit
wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduRxLimit.description: The maximum length of A-MPDU that the radio can receive.

wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduTxLimit.name: wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduTxLimit
wsCcRfRadio11nAmpduTxLimit.description: The maximum length of A-MPDU that the radio can send.

wsCcRfRadioDefault11nTable.name: wsCcRfRadioDefault11nTable
wsCcRfRadioDefault11nTable.description: This table lists the default setting for all supported 11n radios for this wireless switch. A row in this table is an extension of a row in wsCcRfRadioDefaultTable with the relationship being sparse.

wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduMinSpacing.name: wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduMinSpacing
wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduMinSpacing.description: The minimum spacing between the start of adjacent MPDUs within an A-MPDU.

wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduRxLimit.name: wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduRxLimit
wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduRxLimit.description: The maximum length of A-MPDU that the radio can receive.

wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduTxLimit.name: wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduTxLimit
wsCcRfRadioDefault11nAmpduTxLimit.description: The maximum length of A-MPDU that the radio can send.

wsCcRfRadioChannelPower11nTable.name: wsCcRfRadioChannelPower11nTable
wsCcRfRadioChannelPower11nTable.description: This table lists the channel/power/placement properties of 11n radio. A row in this table is an extension of a row in wsCcRfRadioChannelPowerTable with the relationship being sparse.

wsCcRfRadioCp11nChannelWidth.name: wsCcRfRadioCp11nChannelWidth
wsCcRfRadioCp11nChannelWidth.description: The channel width. This object is for 11n radio when wsCcRfRadioCpChannelMode is 'random' or 'acs'. Values of channel width are: 20 MHz - The Legacy mode, single channel is used 40 MHz - Primary and secondary channel chosen The default channel width is 40 MHz.

wsCcRfRadioCp11nSecondaryChannel.name: wsCcRfRadioCp11nSecondaryChannel
wsCcRfRadioCp11nSecondaryChannel.description: The choice for secondary channel. This object is for 11n radio when wsCcRfRadioCpChannelMode is 'fixed'. Values of secondary channel are: none - 20 MHz channel width is used. upper - The upper adjacent channel is used thereby doubling the channel width lower - The lower adjacent channel is used thereby doubling the channel width. The default value is 'none'.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultChannelPower11nTable.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultChannelPower11nTable
wsCcRfRadioDefaultChannelPower11nTable.description: This table lists the default channel/power/placement properties of 11n radio. A row in this table is an extension of a row in wsCcRfRadioDefaultChannelPowerTable with the relationship being sparse.

wsCcRfRadioDefaultCp11nChannelWidth.name: wsCcRfRadioDefaultCp11nChannelWidth
wsCcRfRadioDefaultCp11nChannelWidth.description: The default channel width. This object is for 11n radio when wsCcRfRadioDefaultCpChannelMode is 'random' or 'acs'. Values of channel width are: 20 MHz - The Legacy mode, single channel is used 40 MHz - Primary and secondary channel chosen The default channel width is 40 MHz.

wsCcRfMuCnt.name: wsCcRfMuCnt
wsCcRfMuCnt.description: Number of rows in the wsCcRfMuTable

wsCcRfMuLastMac.name: wsCcRfMuLastMac
wsCcRfMuLastMac.description: This scalar records the MAC address of the most recent mu to be associated/disassociated.

wsCcRfMuTable.name: wsCcRfMuTable
wsCcRfMuTable.description: This table describes general information about each MU serviced by the switch.

wsCcRfMuRadioIndex.name: wsCcRfMuRadioIndex
wsCcRfMuRadioIndex.description: The index of the entry in the wsCcRfRadioTable to which this MU is associated.

wsCcRfMuVlanIndex.name: wsCcRfMuVlanIndex
wsCcRfMuVlanIndex.description: The VLAN that this MU is assigned to.

wsCcRfMuKeyIndex.name: wsCcRfMuKeyIndex
wsCcRfMuKeyIndex.description: The key index using which the MU is sending us frames. Useful when pre-shared keys are used with WEP, as we will know if this MU is

wsCcRfMuBSS.name: wsCcRfMuBSS
wsCcRfMuBSS.description: The BSSID that this MU is associated with.

wsCcRfMuAuthMethod.name: wsCcRfMuAuthMethod
wsCcRfMuAuthMethod.description: Authentication method implemented by the MU.

wsCcRfMuEncMethod.name: wsCcRfMuEncMethod
wsCcRfMuEncMethod.description: Encryption method implemented by the MU.

wsCcRfMuPowerMode.name: wsCcRfMuPowerMode
wsCcRfMuPowerMode.description: Power-mode implemented by the MU. A MU's status will constantly switch between PSP and CAM mode when it is in PSP mode.

wsCcRfMuSupportedRates.name: wsCcRfMuSupportedRates
wsCcRfMuSupportedRates.description: A bit-mask of rates supported by this MU.

wsCcRfMuVoice.name: wsCcRfMuVoice
wsCcRfMuVoice.description: Whether this MU has registered itself as voice-capable.

wsCcRfMuIsDataReady.name: wsCcRfMuIsDataReady
wsCcRfMuIsDataReady.description: This value is true if the wireless switch is ready to forward/switch packets to/from this MU, (internally called the 'data ready' state). Otherwise this value is false.

wsCcRfMuRogueApEna.name: wsCcRfMuRogueApEna
wsCcRfMuRogueApEna.description: If true, this MU supports Rogue AP detection assist algorithm.

wsCcRfMuIsWmm.name: wsCcRfMuIsWmm
wsCcRfMuIsWmm.description: If the MU is using WMM

wsCcRfMuRoamCount.name: wsCcRfMuRoamCount
wsCcRfMuRoamCount.description: Number of times the mu has roamed without de-authentication.

wsCcRfMuLastHeard.name: wsCcRfMuLastHeard
wsCcRfMuLastHeard.description: Timeticks since last heard from MU.

wsCcRfMuDisassociateNow.name: wsCcRfMuDisassociateNow
wsCcRfMuDisassociateNow.description: Setting this value to one initiates the action to disassociate the MU.

wsCcRfMuTunnelIndex.name: wsCcRfMuTunnelIndex
wsCcRfMuTunnelIndex.description: The tunnel identifier for this MU.

wsCcRfMuQosInfo.name: wsCcRfMuQosInfo
wsCcRfMuQosInfo.description: UAPSD parameters for a given MU. Has the following bit values : Bit 0 - UAPSD enabled for Voice AC Bit 1 - UAPSD enabled for Video AC Bit 2 - UAPSD enabled for Best-Effort AC Bit 3 - UAPSD enabled for Background AC Bits 4-5 - UAPSD service period ( 00 - unlimited, 01 - 2 packets, 10 - 4 packets, 11 - 6 packets ).

wsCcRfMuLastAssoc.name: wsCcRfMuLastAssoc
wsCcRfMuLastAssoc.description: Number of seconds elapsed since the last association.

wsCcRfMuRoleName.name: wsCcRfMuRoleName
wsCcRfMuRoleName.description: The name of the role that this MU is assigned with

wsCcRfMuGroup.name: wsCcRfMuGroup
wsCcRfMuGroup.description: Radius user group to which the MU belongs to

wsCcRfMuLocation.name: wsCcRfMuLocation
wsCcRfMuLocation.description: MU is connected from which zone. This information will be provided by SOLE engine.

wsCcRfMuLockOutNow.name: wsCcRfMuLockOutNow
wsCcRfMuLockOutNow.description: Setting this object to one(1) initiates the action to disassociate the MU and set the MAC filter (i.e. associate the ACL) for this MU in one shot.

wsCcRfMuHistoryTimestamp.name: wsCcRfMuHistoryTimestamp
wsCcRfMuHistoryTimestamp.description: The event happened wsCcRfMuHistoryTimestamp seconds ago

wsCfRfMuProbeHistorySignalStrength.name: wsCfRfMuProbeHistorySignalStrength
wsCfRfMuProbeHistorySignalStrength.description: It is not yet decided if this will be reported in db or rssi

wsCcRfMuHistoryEnable.name: wsCcRfMuHistoryEnable
wsCcRfMuHistoryEnable.description: Enable / disable MU history data collection

wsCcRfMuHistoryClear.name: wsCcRfMuHistoryClear
wsCcRfMuHistoryClear.description: Clears the entries in the MU History table.

wsCcRfMuProbeHistoryEnable.name: wsCcRfMuProbeHistoryEnable
wsCcRfMuProbeHistoryEnable.description: Enable / disable MU probe history data collection

wsCcRfMuProbeHistoryClear.name: wsCcRfMuProbeHistoryClear
wsCcRfMuProbeHistoryClear.description: Clears the entries in the MU Probe History table.

wsCcRfMuProbeConfigTable.name: wsCcRfMuProbeConfigTable
wsCcRfMuProbeConfigTable.description: Table to configure MUs that have to be tracked for probe history status

wsCcRfMuProbeConfigMac.name: wsCcRfMuProbeConfigMac
wsCcRfMuProbeConfigMac.description: MAc address of MU to be tracked

wsCcRfMuProbeConfigStatus.name: wsCcRfMuProbeConfigStatus
wsCcRfMuProbeConfigStatus.description: Set tracking on or off for particular MU

wsCcRfMuProbeStatusSignalStrength.name: wsCcRfMuProbeStatusSignalStrength
wsCcRfMuProbeStatusSignalStrength.description: It is not yet decided if this will be reported in db or rssi

wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusMac.name: wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusMac
wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusMac.description: The Mac addres which the user want to view the history status

wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusTable.name: wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusTable
wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusTable.description: wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusTable, the procedure to view the table will be: 1.set the Mac address you are interested in wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusMac 2.do a walk of the table, and it will show you the history of that MU

wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusTimestamp.name: wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusTimestamp
wsCcRfMuHistoryStatusTimestamp.description: The event happened wsCcRfMuHistoryTimestamp seconds ago

wsCcRfMuLocationingPreferredTable.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingPreferredTable
wsCcRfMuLocationingPreferredTable.description: Table having MAC addresses of the preferred MUs. Locationing information for these MUs would be captured/reported.

wsCcRfMuLocationingPreferredEntry.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingPreferredEntry
wsCcRfMuLocationingPreferredEntry.description: An entry for the MU locationing Preferred table

wsCcRfMuLocationingTable.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingTable
wsCcRfMuLocationingTable.description: Table giving locationing information about the various MUs.

wsCcRfMuLocationingEntry.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingEntry
wsCcRfMuLocationingEntry.description: An entry in MU Locationing Table

wsCcRfMuLocationingRadioMac.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingRadioMac
wsCcRfMuLocationingRadioMac.description: The MAC address of the radio that heard the Probe Request from the MU

wsCcRfMuLocationingSignalStrength.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingSignalStrength
wsCcRfMuLocationingSignalStrength.description: The received Signal Strength in dBm

wsCcRfMuLocationingHeardChannel.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingHeardChannel
wsCcRfMuLocationingHeardChannel.description: Channel on which the MU Probe Request was heard

wsCcRfMuLocationingHeardTime.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingHeardTime
wsCcRfMuLocationingHeardTime.description: Time in timeticks (since boot), when the MU Probe Request was heard

wsCcRfMuLocationingMaxMus.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingMaxMus
wsCcRfMuLocationingMaxMus.description: Maximum number of MUs for MU locationing table.

wsCcRfMuLocationingWindowTime.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingWindowTime
wsCcRfMuLocationingWindowTime.description: Time window in seconds to collect the MU probe requests for a MU-Radio pair

wsCcRfMuLocationingNumMu.name: wsCcRfMuLocationingNumMu
wsCcRfMuLocationingNumMu.description: Current number of MUs in the table.

wsCcRfMuRateLimitingUp.name: wsCcRfMuRateLimitingUp
wsCcRfMuRateLimitingUp.description: Rate limit in uplink direction, from wireless client to network. The rate is in the range of <100-100000> kbps. The value 0 means that rate limiting is disabled.

wsCcRfMuRateLimitingDown.name: wsCcRfMuRateLimitingDown
wsCcRfMuRateLimitingDown.description: Rate limit in downlink direction, from network to wireless client. The rate is in the range of <100-100000> kbps. The value 0 means that rate limiting is disabled.

wsCcRfMuLoadBalancingMethod.name: wsCcRfMuLoadBalancingMethod
wsCcRfMuLoadBalancingMethod.description: Configure the MUs to be load balanced by user count or by by radio throughput threshold.

wsCcRfWlanTable.name: wsCcRfWlanTable
wsCcRfWlanTable.description: Table of wireless LANs on the switch.

wsCcRfWlanEnable.name: wsCcRfWlanEnable
wsCcRfWlanEnable.description: Enable/Disable wireless Lan. If this wlan is referenced by wsCcRfRadioBssWlanMap, a set to disabled mode will fail.

wsCcRfWlanVlan.name: wsCcRfWlanVlan
wsCcRfWlanVlan.description: The Vlan this Wlan is associated with. If not associated with any Vlan, this value will be 0. This object's functionality has now been replaced with wsCcRfWlanVlanTable, which allows to configure upto 32 VLANs per WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanDisallowMuToMu.name: wsCcRfWlanDisallowMuToMu
wsCcRfWlanDisallowMuToMu.description: Set to true to prohibit MU-to-MU communication.

wsCcRfWlanSecBeacon.name: wsCcRfWlanSecBeacon
wsCcRfWlanSecBeacon.description: Enable the Secure Beacon checkbox to disallow the Access Port from broadcasting an ESSID in its beacons. This is a safeguard to prevent intruders from tapping into the WLAN. Consider this security measure for a private, corporate network.

wsCcRfWlanWeight.name: wsCcRfWlanWeight
wsCcRfWlanWeight.description: The weight to be used when QoS for all WLANs is set to weighted-round-robin. Note that the sum of all weights across all WLANs need not total 100.

wsCcRfWlanWmmEnable.name: wsCcRfWlanWmmEnable
wsCcRfWlanWmmEnable.description: Enable/Disable WMM on this wireless LAN

wsCcRfWlanSvpEnable.name: wsCcRfWlanSvpEnable
wsCcRfWlanSvpEnable.description: Enable/Disable support for Spectralink Voice Prioritization on this wireless LAN

wsCcRfWlanAuthentication.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthentication
wsCcRfWlanAuthentication.description: If auth802dot1xEap, additional EAP settings for this WLAN will be used from the matching entry in the wireless authentication.

wsCcRfWlanEncryptionMap.name: wsCcRfWlanEncryptionMap
wsCcRfWlanEncryptionMap.description: ** this needs to be a bitmap of enc types ** If cryptoWep64 or cryptoWep128, additional WEP settings for this WLAN will be used from the matching entry in the ccWlanCryptoWepTable. Likewise, if cryptoWpaTkip, use the settings in the matching entry in the ccWlanCryptoWpaTable. Likewise, if cryptoKeyguardMcm, use the settings in the matching entry in the ccWlanCryptoKeyguardTable.

wsCcRfWlanBcastEnc.name: wsCcRfWlanBcastEnc
wsCcRfWlanBcastEnc.description: The broadcast encryption type in use on a WLAN. In most cases it is same as the unicast encryption type. When multiple encryption types are supported (TKIP+CCMP) it is usually the lowest encryption type.

wsCcRfWlanMuIdleTime.name: wsCcRfWlanMuIdleTime
wsCcRfWlanMuIdleTime.description: The number of seconds for which if the switch does not receive/send any data frames from/to an MU, it disassociates the MU. If an MU roams away from an access point without disassociating, this timeout helps the switch determine that the MU is gone, and clear resources allocated for that MU.

wsCcRfWlanMuToMu.name: wsCcRfWlanMuToMu
wsCcRfWlanMuToMu.description: States the mode of operation for MU-to-MU communications in the wireless switch. drop(1): traffic is not relayed to other MUs. allow(2): traffic is relayed to other MUs. The value switchToWired(3) is deprecated. Using switchToWired(3) is identical in behavior to the value allow(2).

wsCcRfWlanQosPrioritization.name: wsCcRfWlanQosPrioritization
wsCcRfWlanQosPrioritization.description: Sets the prioritization of the WLAN for QoS purposes.

wsCcRfWlanDynamicVlanAssignment.name: wsCcRfWlanDynamicVlanAssignment
wsCcRfWlanDynamicVlanAssignment.description: Enables or disables dynamic VLAN assignment for the WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanAccountingType.name: wsCcRfWlanAccountingType
wsCcRfWlanAccountingType.description: Indicates if the accounting type is Radius, Syslog or turned off.

wsCcRfWlanSyslogServerIp.name: wsCcRfWlanSyslogServerIp
wsCcRfWlanSyslogServerIp.description: IP Address of the Syslog server

wsCcRfWlanNacMode.name: wsCcRfWlanNacMode
wsCcRfWlanNacMode.description: Set NAC mode to 1. Do NAC validation for all MU's except one in exclude list 2. By pass NAC validation for all MU's but include those that are in include list 3. No NAC operation. Go thru RADIUS server if authentication is set to EAP

wsCcRfWlanQosWeight.name: wsCcRfWlanQosWeight
wsCcRfWlanQosWeight.description: Sets the weight of a WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanHoldTime.name: wsCcRfWlanHoldTime
wsCcRfWlanHoldTime.description: Hold time in seconds. The user credentials would hold for this much time when it leaves or roams away.

wsCcRfWlanIndependentModeEnable.name: wsCcRfWlanIndependentModeEnable
wsCcRfWlanIndependentModeEnable.description: If true, it means that the Independent mode for this WLAN is enabled. That allows it to be used by AAPs. A false value means that the WLAN is in 'regular' mode and cannot be used for AAPs.

wsCcRfWlanClientBridgeBackhaulEnable.name: wsCcRfWlanClientBridgeBackhaulEnable
wsCcRfWlanClientBridgeBackhaulEnable.description: Enable client bridge backhaul. Requires wsCcRfWlanIndependentModeEnable to be True for this flag to be enabled.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapTable.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapTable
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapTable.description: Table of EAP authentication settings for each WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerIp1.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerIp1
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerIp1.description: IP address of the 1st RADIUS server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerPort1.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerPort1
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerPort1.description: Port number of the 1st RADIUS server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerSecret1.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerSecret1
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerSecret1.description: Shared secret of the 1st RADIUS server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerIp2.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerIp2
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerIp2.description: IP address of the 2nd RADIUS server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerPort2.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerPort2
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerPort2.description: Port number of the 2nd RADIUS server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerSecret2.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerSecret2
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusServerSecret2.description: Shared secret of the 2nd RADIUS server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapAuthProtocol.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapAuthProtocol
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapAuthProtocol.description: The authentication protocol to be used, PAP or CHAP.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapDscpTos.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapDscpTos
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapDscpTos.description: DSCP or TOS value to be used (between 0 and 63).

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapAccountingMode.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapAccountingMode
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapAccountingMode.description: Indicates if mode of accounting is one of: Start-Stop, Start-only or Start-interim-Stop

wsCcRfWlanAuthPrimaryServer.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthPrimaryServer
wsCcRfWlanAuthPrimaryServer.description: IP Address of the Primary Accounting Server

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondaryServer.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondaryServer
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondaryServer.description: IP Address of the Secondary Accounting Server

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapPrimarySrvrPort.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapPrimarySrvrPort
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapPrimarySrvrPort.description: Port Number of the Primary Server

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondarySrvrPort.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondarySrvrPort
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondarySrvrPort.description: Port Number of the Secondary Server

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapPrimarySecret.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapPrimarySecret
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapPrimarySecret.description: Shared secret of the Primary Accounting server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondarySecret.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondarySecret
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapSecondarySecret.description: Shared secret of the Secondary Accounting server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusMacAuthFormat.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusMacAuthFormat
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusMacAuthFormat.description: The format of the MAC address to be sent to a RADIUS server when using MAC authentication: no-delim: No Delimiter - AABBCCDDEEFF pair-colon: Colon Delmilter per Pair - AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF pair-dash: Dash Delimiter per Pair - AA-BB-CC-DD-EE-FF quad-dot: Dot Delimiter per Four Hex - AABB.CCDD.EEFF middle-dash: Dash Delmiter in the middle - AABBCC-DDEEFF

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusDynamicAuthEnable.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusDynamicAuthEnable
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapRadiusDynamicAuthEnable.description: Enable support for Radius Dynamic Authorization extensions such as Disconnect Message, and Change-Of-Authorization, as described in RFC 3576

wsCcRfWlanAuthKerberosTable.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthKerberosTable
wsCcRfWlanAuthKerberosTable.description: Table of Kerberos authentication settings for each WLAN.

wsCcRfwlanAuthKerbRealm.name: wsCcRfwlanAuthKerbRealm
wsCcRfwlanAuthKerbRealm.description: Realm name. A realm name functions similarly to a DNS domain name. In theory, the realm name is arbitrary. However, in practice a Kerberos realm is named by uppercasing the DNS domain name that is associated with hosts in the realm.

wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerIp1.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerIp1
wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerIp1.description: IP address of the 1st Kerberos server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerPort1.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerPort1
wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerPort1.description: Port number of the 1st Kerberos server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerIp2.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerIp2
wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerIp2.description: IP address of the 2nd Kerberos server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerPort2.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerPort2
wsCcRfWlanAuthKerbKdcServerPort2.description: Port number of the 2nd Kerberos server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerTable.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerTable
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerTable.description: Table of Exclude lists EAP authentication settings for each WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerIp1.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerIp1
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerIp1.description: IP address of the 1st NAC server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort1.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort1
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort1.description: Port number of the 1st NAC server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerSecret1.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerSecret1
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerSecret1.description: Shared secret of the 1st NAC server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerIp2.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerIp2
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerIp2.description: IP address of the 2nd NAC server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort2.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort2
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerPort2.description: Port number of the 2nd NAC server.

wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerSecret2.name: wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerSecret2
wsCcRfWlanAuthEapNACServerSecret2.description: Shared secret of the 2nd NAC server.

wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Table.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Table
wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Table.description: Table of WEP encryption settings for each WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanEncWep64KeyIndex.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep64KeyIndex
wsCcRfWlanEncWep64KeyIndex.description: Specifies which WEP key to use.

wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key1.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key1
wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key1.description: WEP key #1 exactly 5 octets for WEP-64 (40-bit key).

wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key2.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key2
wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key2.description: WEP key #2 exactly 5 octets for WEP-64 (40-bit key).

wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key3.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key3
wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key3.description: WEP key #3 exactly 5 octets for WEP-64 (40-bit key).

wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key4.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key4
wsCcRfWlanEncWep64Key4.description: WEP key #4 exactly 5 octets for WEP-64 (40-bit key).

wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgTable.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgTable
wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgTable.description: Table of WEP encryption settings for each WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKeyIndex.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKeyIndex
wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKeyIndex.description: Specifies which WEP key to use.

wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey1.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey1
wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey1.description: WEP key #1 exactly 13 octets for WEP-128 (104-bit key);

wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey2.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey2
wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey2.description: WEP key #2 exactly 13 octets for WEP-128 (104-bit key);

wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey3.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey3
wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey3.description: WEP key #3 exactly 13 octets for WEP-128 (104-bit key);

wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey4.name: wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey4
wsCcRfWlanEncWep128KgKey4.description: WEP key #4 exactly 13 octets for WEP-128 (104-bit key);

wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpTable.name: wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpTable
wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpTable.description: Table of Tkip/Ccmp encryption settings for each WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyType.name: wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyType
wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyType.description: Specify whether to use key or passphrase.

wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyRotation.name: wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyRotation
wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyRotation.description: A truth-value that indicates whether the group key for a TKIP/CCMP mobile-unit should be periodically rotated.

wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyInterval.name: wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyInterval
wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpKeyInterval.description: The number of seconds after which the broadcast key of all mobile-units on a particular wireless lan is replaced by a new broadcast key.

wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpPmkCaching.name: wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpPmkCaching
wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpPmkCaching.description: Whether IEEE 802.11i PMK caching is enabled. Use of PMK caching allows a mobile-unit to authenticate just once to an AP, even if it roams away from it, and roams back to it. Enabling this feature results in much faster roam times on wireless LANs that use 802.1x authentication.

wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpOppPmkCaching.name: wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpOppPmkCaching
wsCcRfWlanEncTkipCcmpOppPmkCaching.description: Whether extensions to IEEE 802.11i PMK caching, known as opportunistic PMK caching, are enabled. It extends PMK caching (authenticate once to an AP) to the whole switch (authenticate once to a switch). Enabling this feature results in much faster roam times on wireless LANs that use 802.1x authentication

wsCcRfWlanEncP2WPassphrase.name: wsCcRfWlanEncP2WPassphrase
wsCcRfWlanEncP2WPassphrase.description: An input to an algorithm used to convert ascii into wep keys.

wsCcRfWlanEncP2WClearKeys.name: wsCcRfWlanEncP2WClearKeys
wsCcRfWlanEncP2WClearKeys.description: Setting this scalar to 1 will clear all wep key fields.

wsCcRfWlanWmmTable.name: wsCcRfWlanWmmTable
wsCcRfWlanWmmTable.description: Configuration parameters for 802.11e / Wireless MultiMedia, which control the Quality of Service between the wireless devices on the network

wsCcRfWlanWmmBeParm.name: wsCcRfWlanWmmBeParm
wsCcRfWlanWmmBeParm.description: Parameters for the Best Effort QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. Prior to setting this field, please be sure to get the current value.

wsCcRfWlanWmmBkParm.name: wsCcRfWlanWmmBkParm
wsCcRfWlanWmmBkParm.description: Parameters for the Background QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. Prior to setting this field, please be sure to get the current value.

wsCcRfWlanWmmViParm.name: wsCcRfWlanWmmViParm
wsCcRfWlanWmmViParm.description: Parameters for the Video QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. Prior to setting this field, please be sure to get the current value.

wsCcRfWlanWmmVoParm.name: wsCcRfWlanWmmVoParm
wsCcRfWlanWmmVoParm.description: Parameters for the Voice QoS category of traffic in an 802.11e network. Prior to setting this field, please be sure to get the current value.

wsCcRfWlanCount.name: wsCcRfWlanCount
wsCcRfWlanCount.description: the current number of wlan in the system

wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListTable.name: wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListTable
wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListTable.description: Configuration for Include lists and hosts. The host entries existing in this list will go through NAC check if this client include list name is added into WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListEntry.name: wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListEntry
wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListEntry.description: Include list and host entry contains information about host mac address and mac mask to include for NAC status check.

wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListHostName.name: wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListHostName
wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListHostName.description: String index of Mu host names for the WlanClientIncludeListTable.

wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListMAC.name: wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListMAC
wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListMAC.description: Host MAC address. This is a MAC address of the Mobile Units. Example: 00:0A:12:34:BE:OF

wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListMACMask.name: wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListMACMask
wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListMACMask.description: Host end MAC address. This field is used to specify the range of MAC addresses. Example: 00:0A:12:34:BE:FF

wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListRowStatus.name: wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListRowStatus
wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListRowStatus.description: Create or Delete a row from Include list Table.

wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListTable.name: wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListTable
wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListTable.description: Configuration for Exclude lists and hosts. The host entries existing in this list will not go through NAC check if its associated to the particular WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListEntry.name: wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListEntry
wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListEntry.description: Exclude list and host entry contains information about host mac address and mac mask to exclude from NAC operation.

wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListHostName.name: wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListHostName
wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListHostName.description: String index of Mu host names for the WlanClientExcludeListTable.

wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListMAC.name: wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListMAC
wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListMAC.description: Host MAC address. This is a MAC address of the Mobile Units. Example: 00:0A:12:34:BE:OF

wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListMACMask.name: wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListMACMask
wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListMACMask.description: Host end MAC address. This field is used to specify the range of MAC addresses. Example: 00:0A:12:34:BE:FF

wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListRowStatus.name: wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListRowStatus
wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListRowStatus.description: Create or Delete a row from Exclude list Table.

wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanMapTable.name: wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanMapTable
wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanMapTable.description: Configure wlan mapping for this client list. The list could be include or exclude list name.

wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanMapEntry.name: wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanMapEntry
wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanMapEntry.description: This table will allow the user to associate client exclude and include lists to each WLAN.

wsCcRfWlanClientListName.name: wsCcRfWlanClientListName
wsCcRfWlanClientListName.description: Client exclude and include list name(s). This is a read only index which will display all the exclude and include list names created before (in wsCcRfWlanClientIncludeListTable and wsCcRfWlanClientExcludeListTable).

wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanBitmap.name: wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanBitmap
wsCcRfWlanClientListWlanBitmap.description: Adding client list (include and exclude list) to wlan(s). This is bitmap value (which is from 1 to maximum wlans ie., 1-256).

wsCcRfWlanVlanTable.name: wsCcRfWlanVlanTable
wsCcRfWlanVlanTable.description: Table of Vlans assigned to parent Wlan

wsCcRfWlanVlanIndex.name: wsCcRfWlanVlanIndex
wsCcRfWlanVlanIndex.description: The numeric vlan ID for this vlan entry, valid range is [ 1, 4094 ].

wsCcRfWlanVlanUserLimit.name: wsCcRfWlanVlanUserLimit
wsCcRfWlanVlanUserLimit.description: The maximum number of users that can be associated on this VLAN of the WLAN. The value 0 has a special meaning. It means no limit on this VLAN of the WLAN. Other limits, such as maximum number of users per radio, etc, would still apply. Also, the maximum number of users is limited by the maximum number of MUs supported by the wireless switch e.g. 4096 for WS5100, 8192 for RFS7000. The range given here is the upper limit for any WiOS platform.

wsCcRfWlanVlanRowStatus.name: wsCcRfWlanVlanRowStatus
wsCcRfWlanVlanRowStatus.description: At the time of row-creation, rowStatus is set to createAndGo(4). If user does not wish to have this vlanIndex mapped to a WLAN any more, user deletes the row by setting rowstatus to destroy(6). When a walk is done on this table, it will show one row for each vlan-wlan mapping and the rowStatus of all those rows will be active(1).

wsCcRfWlanMaxVlans.name: wsCcRfWlanMaxVlans
wsCcRfWlanMaxVlans.description: Maximum number of vlans per wlan.

wsCcRfWlanVlanLastError.name: wsCcRfWlanVlanLastError
wsCcRfWlanVlanLastError.description: The last error message on vlan table operation. It is not cleared.

wsCcRfWlanBwAllocationEnable.name: wsCcRfWlanBwAllocationEnable
wsCcRfWlanBwAllocationEnable.description: Enables or Disables Wlan Bandwidth Allocation.

wsCcRfMuAssocAclTable.name: wsCcRfMuAssocAclTable
wsCcRfMuAssocAclTable.description: A table that allows users to filter MUs that are allowed/denied association to different WLANs based on their MAC address

wsCcRfMuAssocAclMode.name: wsCcRfMuAssocAclMode
wsCcRfMuAssocAclMode.description: Allow or deny the Mac range specified by wsCcRfWlanMuAclStartingMac and wsCcRfWlanMuAclEndingMac.

wsCcRfMuAssocAclStartingMac.name: wsCcRfMuAssocAclStartingMac
wsCcRfMuAssocAclStartingMac.description: Starting MAC address in a range or addresses.

wsCcRfMuAssocAclEndingMac.name: wsCcRfMuAssocAclEndingMac
wsCcRfMuAssocAclEndingMac.description: Ending MAC address in a range of addresses.

wsCcRfMuAssocAclWlans.name: wsCcRfMuAssocAclWlans
wsCcRfMuAssocAclWlans.description: The list of WLANs that this ACL rule applies to

wsCcRfRapMaxRogue.name: wsCcRfRapMaxRogue
wsCcRfRapMaxRogue.description: The maximum number of rows in wsCcRfRapStatusTable

wsCcRfRapTimeout.name: wsCcRfRapTimeout
wsCcRfRapTimeout.description: The amount of time a rogue AP will remain after it is no longer seen

wsCcRfRapStatusTable.name: wsCcRfRapStatusTable
wsCcRfRapStatusTable.description: Status of AP assisted approved and un-approved access ports

wsCcRfRapStatusMac.name: wsCcRfRapStatusMac
wsCcRfRapStatusMac.description: Mac address of the access port

wsCcRfRapStatusHeardAp.name: wsCcRfRapStatusHeardAp
wsCcRfRapStatusHeardAp.description: Index of the heard access port

wsCcRfRapStatusLastTimeSeen.name: wsCcRfRapStatusLastTimeSeen
wsCcRfRapStatusLastTimeSeen.description: The number of second(s) ago this ap was last seen.

wsCcRfRapStatusLastSignal.name: wsCcRfRapStatusLastSignal
wsCcRfRapStatusLastSignal.description: Last signal level from the radio.

wsCcRfRapStatusMinSignal.name: wsCcRfRapStatusMinSignal
wsCcRfRapStatusMinSignal.description: Weakest signal heard from this radio.

wsCcRfRapStatusMaxSignal.name: wsCcRfRapStatusMaxSignal
wsCcRfRapStatusMaxSignal.description: Strongest signal heard from this radio.

wsCcRfRapStatusSumSignal.name: wsCcRfRapStatusSumSignal
wsCcRfRapStatusSumSignal.description: Sum of all signal values for this radio.

wsCcRfRapStatusSignalCount.name: wsCcRfRapStatusSignalCount
wsCcRfRapStatusSignalCount.description: Number of signal data points for this radio.

wsCcRfRapMuAssistRefreshPeriod.name: wsCcRfRapMuAssistRefreshPeriod
wsCcRfRapMuAssistRefreshPeriod.description: The period in seconds with which all scan-capable mobile-units are requested to scan for neighboring APs

wsCcRfRUnpprovedApTimeout.name: wsCcRfRUnpprovedApTimeout
wsCcRfRUnpprovedApTimeout.description: The amount of time an unapproved AP will remain after it is no longer seen

wsCcRfRApprovedApTimeout.name: wsCcRfRApprovedApTimeout
wsCcRfRApprovedApTimeout.description: The amount of time an approved AP will remain after it is no longer seen

wsCcRfRapMuAssistTable.name: wsCcRfRapMuAssistTable
wsCcRfRapMuAssistTable.description: Status of MU assisted un-approved access ports
